{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to talk to you"},{"time":2000,"text":"about one of the biggest myths in medicine,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and that is the idea"},{"time":6000,"text":"that all we need are more medical breakthroughs"},{"time":9000,"text":"and then all of our problems will be solved."},{"time":12000,"text":"Our society loves to romanticize"},{"time":15000,"text":"the idea of the single, solo inventor"},{"time":17000,"text":"who, working late in the lab one night,"},{"time":20000,"text":"makes an earthshaking discovery,"},{"time":23000,"text":"and voila, overnight everything's changed."},{"time":27000,"text":"That's a very appealing picture,"},{"time":29000,"text":"however, it's just not true."},{"time":32000,"text":"In fact, medicine today is a team sport."},{"time":35000,"text":"And in many ways,"},{"time":37000,"text":"it always has been."},{"time":39000,"text":"I'd like to share with you a story"},{"time":41000,"text":"about how I've experienced this very dramatically"},{"time":44000,"text":"in my own work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46000,"text":"I'm a surgeon,"},{"time":48000,"text":"and we surgeons have always had"},{"time":50000,"text":"this special relationship with light."},{"time":53000,"text":"When I make an incision inside a patient's body, it's dark."},{"time":57000,"text":"We need to shine light to see what we're doing."},{"time":60000,"text":"And this is why, traditionally,"},{"time":63000,"text":"surgeries have always started so early in the morning --"},{"time":65000,"text":"to take advantage of daylight hours."},{"time":67000,"text":"And if you look at historical pictures"},{"time":69000,"text":"of the early operating rooms,"},{"time":71000,"text":"they have been on top of buildings."},{"time":74000,"text":"For example, this is the oldest operating room in the Western world,"},{"time":76000,"text":"in London,"},{"time":78000,"text":"where the operating room"},{"time":80000,"text":"is actually on top of a church"},{"time":82000,"text":"with a skylight coming in."},{"time":84000,"text":"And then this is a picture"},{"time":86000,"text":"of one of the most famous hospitals in America."},{"time":89000,"text":"This is Mass General in Boston."},{"time":91000,"text":"And do you know where the operating room is?"},{"time":93000,"text":"Here it is"},{"time":95000,"text":"on the top of the building"},{"time":97000,"text":"with plenty of windows to let light in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100000,"text":"So nowadays in the operating room,"},{"time":102000,"text":"we no longer need to use sunlight."},{"time":105000,"text":"And because we no longer need to use sunlight,"},{"time":108000,"text":"we have very specialized lights"},{"time":110000,"text":"that are made for the operating room."},{"time":112000,"text":"We have an opportunity"},{"time":114000,"text":"to bring in other kinds of lights --"},{"time":116000,"text":"lights that can allow us to see"},{"time":118000,"text":"what we currently don't see."},{"time":121000,"text":"And this is what I think"},{"time":123000,"text":"is the magic of fluorescence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125000,"text":"So let me back up a little bit."},{"time":127000,"text":"When we are in medical school,"},{"time":130000,"text":"we learn our anatomy from illustrations such as this"},{"time":133000,"text":"where everything's color-coded."},{"time":136000,"text":"Nerves are yellow, arteries are red,"},{"time":138000,"text":"veins are blue."},{"time":140000,"text":"That's so easy anybody could become a surgeon, right?"},{"time":144000,"text":"However, when we have a real patient on the table,"},{"time":147000,"text":"this is the same neck dissection --"},{"time":150000,"text":"not so easy to tell the difference"},{"time":152000,"text":"between different structures."},{"time":154000,"text":"We heard over the last couple days"},{"time":157000,"text":"what an urgent problem"},{"time":159000,"text":"cancer still is in our society,"},{"time":161000,"text":"what a pressing need it is"},{"time":163000,"text":"for us to not have"},{"time":165000,"text":"one person die every minute."},{"time":169000,"text":"Well if cancer can be caught early,"},{"time":171000,"text":"enough such that someone can have their cancer taken out,"},{"time":176000,"text":"excised with surgery,"},{"time":178000,"text":"I don't care if it has this gene or that gene,"},{"time":180000,"text":"or if it has this protein or that protein,"},{"time":182000,"text":"it's in the jar."},{"time":184000,"text":"It's done, it's out, you're cured of cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187000,"text":"This is how we excise cancers."},{"time":189000,"text":"We do our best, based upon our training"},{"time":192000,"text":"and the way the cancer looks and the way it feels"},{"time":195000,"text":"and its relationship to other structures and all of our experience,"},{"time":198000,"text":"we say, you know what, the cancer's gone."},{"time":201000,"text":"We've made a good job. We've taken it out."},{"time":204000,"text":"That's what the surgeon is saying in the operating room"},{"time":206000,"text":"when the patient's on the table."},{"time":208000,"text":"But then we actually don't know that it's all out."},{"time":211000,"text":"We actually have to take samples from the surgical bed,"},{"time":214000,"text":"what's left behind in the patient,"},{"time":216000,"text":"and then send those bits to the pathology lab."},{"time":220000,"text":"In the meanwhile, the patient's on the operating room table."},{"time":222000,"text":"The nurses, anesthesiologist, the surgeon,"},{"time":224000,"text":"all the assistants are waiting around."},{"time":226000,"text":"And we wait."},{"time":228000,"text":"The pathologist takes that sample,"},{"time":230000,"text":"freezes it, cuts it, looks in the microscope one by one"},{"time":233000,"text":"and then calls back into the room."},{"time":235000,"text":"And that may be 20 minutes later per piece."},{"time":237000,"text":"So if you've sent three specimens,"},{"time":239000,"text":"it's an hour later."},{"time":241000,"text":"And very often they say,"},{"time":243000,"text":"\"You know what, points A and B are okay,"},{"time":246000,"text":"but point C, you still have some residual cancer there."},{"time":248000,"text":"Please go cut that piece out.\""},{"time":251000,"text":"So we go back and we do that again, and again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254000,"text":"And this whole process:"},{"time":256000,"text":"\"Okay you're done."},{"time":258000,"text":"We think the entire tumor is out.\""},{"time":260000,"text":"But very often several days later,"},{"time":263000,"text":"the patient's gone home,"},{"time":265000,"text":"we get a phone call:"},{"time":267000,"text":"\"I'm sorry,"},{"time":269000,"text":"once we looked at the final pathology,"},{"time":271000,"text":"once we looked at the final specimen,"},{"time":273000,"text":"we actually found that there's a couple other spots"},{"time":276000,"text":"where the margins are positive."},{"time":279000,"text":"There's still cancer in your patient.\""},{"time":282000,"text":"So now you're faced with telling your patient, first of all,"},{"time":285000,"text":"that they may need another surgery,"},{"time":287000,"text":"or that they need additional therapy"},{"time":289000,"text":"such as radiation or chemotherapy."},{"time":293000,"text":"So wouldn't it be better"},{"time":295000,"text":"if we could really tell,"},{"time":297000,"text":"if the surgeon could really tell,"},{"time":300000,"text":"whether or not there's still cancer on the surgical field?"},{"time":303000,"text":"I mean, in many ways, the way that we're doing it,"},{"time":306000,"text":"we're still operating in the dark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310000,"text":"So in 2004, during my surgical residency,"},{"time":313000,"text":"I had the great fortune"},{"time":315000,"text":"to meet Dr. Roger Tsien,"},{"time":318000,"text":"who went on to win the Nobel Prize for chemistry"},{"time":321000,"text":"in 2008."},{"time":323000,"text":"Roger and his team"},{"time":325000,"text":"were working on a way to detect cancer,"},{"time":328000,"text":"and they had a very clever molecule"},{"time":330000,"text":"that they had come up with."},{"time":332000,"text":"The molecule they had developed"},{"time":334000,"text":"had three parts."},{"time":336000,"text":"The main part of it is the blue part, polycation,"},{"time":339000,"text":"and it's basically very sticky"},{"time":341000,"text":"to every tissue in your body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343000,"text":"So imagine that you make a solution"},{"time":345000,"text":"full of this sticky material"},{"time":347000,"text":"and inject it into the veins of someone who has cancer,"},{"time":349000,"text":"everything's going to get lit up."},{"time":351000,"text":"Nothing will be specific."},{"time":353000,"text":"There's no specificity there."},{"time":355000,"text":"So they added two additional components."},{"time":357000,"text":"The first one is a polyanionic segment,"},{"time":360000,"text":"which basically acts as a non-stick backing"},{"time":362000,"text":"like the back of a sticker."},{"time":364000,"text":"So when those two are together, the molecule is neutral"},{"time":367000,"text":"and nothing gets stuck down."},{"time":369000,"text":"And the two pieces are then linked"},{"time":372000,"text":"by something that can only be cut"},{"time":375000,"text":"if you have the right molecular scissors --"},{"time":377000,"text":"for example, the kind of protease enzymes"},{"time":379000,"text":"that tumors make."},{"time":381000,"text":"So here in this situation,"},{"time":383000,"text":"if you make a solution full of this three-part molecule"},{"time":387000,"text":"along with the dye, which is shown in green,"},{"time":389000,"text":"and you inject it into the vein"},{"time":392000,"text":"of someone who has cancer,"},{"time":394000,"text":"normal tissue can't cut it."},{"time":396000,"text":"The molecule passes through and gets excreted."},{"time":399000,"text":"However, in the presence of the tumor,"},{"time":401000,"text":"now there are molecular scissors"},{"time":403000,"text":"that can break this molecule apart"},{"time":405000,"text":"right there at the cleavable site."},{"time":407000,"text":"And now, boom,"},{"time":409000,"text":"the tumor labels itself"},{"time":411000,"text":"and it gets fluorescent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"So here's an example of a nerve"},{"time":416000,"text":"that has tumor surrounding it."},{"time":418000,"text":"Can you tell where the tumor is?"},{"time":420000,"text":"I couldn't when I was working on this."},{"time":423000,"text":"But here it is. It's fluorescent."},{"time":425000,"text":"Now it's green."},{"time":427000,"text":"See, so every single one in the audience"},{"time":430000,"text":"now can tell where the cancer is."},{"time":433000,"text":"We can tell in the operating room, in the field,"},{"time":436000,"text":"at a molecular level,"},{"time":438000,"text":"where is the cancer and what the surgeon needs to do"},{"time":440000,"text":"and how much more work they need to do"},{"time":442000,"text":"to cut that out."},{"time":445000,"text":"And the cool thing about fluorescence"},{"time":447000,"text":"is that it's not only bright,"},{"time":450000,"text":"it actually can shine through tissue."},{"time":453000,"text":"The light that the fluorescence emits"},{"time":456000,"text":"can go through tissue."},{"time":458000,"text":"So even if the tumor is not right on the surface,"},{"time":461000,"text":"you'll still be able to see it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"In this movie, you can see"},{"time":466000,"text":"that the tumor is green."},{"time":469000,"text":"There's actually normal muscle on top of it. See that?"},{"time":472000,"text":"And I'm peeling that muscle away."},{"time":474000,"text":"But even before I peel that muscle away,"},{"time":476000,"text":"you saw that there was a tumor underneath."},{"time":479000,"text":"So that's the beauty of having a tumor"},{"time":482000,"text":"that's labeled with fluorescent molecules."},{"time":485000,"text":"That you can, not only see the margins"},{"time":487000,"text":"right there on a molecular level,"},{"time":489000,"text":"but you can see it even if it's not right on the top --"},{"time":492000,"text":"even if it's beyond your field of view."},{"time":495000,"text":"And this works for metastatic lymph nodes also."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498000,"text":"Sentinel lymph node dissection"},{"time":500000,"text":"has really changed the way that we manage breast cancer, melanoma."},{"time":504000,"text":"Women used to get"},{"time":506000,"text":"really debilitating surgeries"},{"time":508000,"text":"to excise all of the axillary lymph nodes."},{"time":511000,"text":"But when sentinel lymph node"},{"time":514000,"text":"came into our treatment protocol,"},{"time":517000,"text":"the surgeon basically looks for the single node"},{"time":520000,"text":"that is the first draining lymph node of the cancer."},{"time":523000,"text":"And then if that node has cancer,"},{"time":526000,"text":"the woman would go on to get"},{"time":528000,"text":"the axillary lymph node dissection."},{"time":530000,"text":"So what that means"},{"time":532000,"text":"is if the lymph node did not have cancer,"},{"time":535000,"text":"the woman would be saved"},{"time":537000,"text":"from having unnecessary surgery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"But sentinel lymph node, the way that we do it today,"},{"time":542000,"text":"is kind of like having a road map"},{"time":544000,"text":"just to know where to go."},{"time":546000,"text":"So if you're driving on the freeway"},{"time":548000,"text":"and you want to know where's the next gas station,"},{"time":550000,"text":"you have a map to tell you that that gas station is down the road."},{"time":553000,"text":"It doesn't tell you whether or not"},{"time":555000,"text":"the gas station has gas."},{"time":557000,"text":"You have to cut it out, bring it back home,"},{"time":560000,"text":"cut it up, look inside"},{"time":562000,"text":"and say, \"Oh yes, it does have gas.\""},{"time":564000,"text":"So that takes more time."},{"time":566000,"text":"Patients are still on the operating room table."},{"time":568000,"text":"Anesthesiologists, surgeons are waiting around."},{"time":570000,"text":"That takes time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"So with our technology, we can tell right away."},{"time":575000,"text":"You see a lot of little, roundish bumps there."},{"time":578000,"text":"Some of these are swollen lymph nodes"},{"time":581000,"text":"that look a little larger than others."},{"time":583000,"text":"Who amongst us hasn't had swollen lymph nodes with a cold?"},{"time":586000,"text":"That doesn't mean that there's cancer inside."},{"time":588000,"text":"Well with our technology,"},{"time":590000,"text":"the surgeon is able to tell immediately"},{"time":593000,"text":"which nodes have cancer."},{"time":595000,"text":"I won't go into this very much,"},{"time":597000,"text":"but our technology, besides being able"},{"time":599000,"text":"to tag tumor and metastatic lymph nodes with fluorescence,"},{"time":603000,"text":"we can also use the same smart three-part molecule"},{"time":607000,"text":"to tag gadolinium onto the system"},{"time":610000,"text":"so you can do this noninvasively."},{"time":612000,"text":"The patient has cancer,"},{"time":614000,"text":"you want to know if the lymph nodes have cancer"},{"time":616000,"text":"even before you go in."},{"time":618000,"text":"Well you can see this on an MRI."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621000,"text":"So in surgery,"},{"time":623000,"text":"it's important to know what to cut out."},{"time":626000,"text":"But equally important"},{"time":628000,"text":"is to preserve things"},{"time":631000,"text":"that are important for function."},{"time":634000,"text":"So it's very important to avoid inadvertent injury."},{"time":637000,"text":"And what I'm talking about"},{"time":639000,"text":"are nerves."},{"time":641000,"text":"Nerves, if they are injured,"},{"time":643000,"text":"can cause paralysis,"},{"time":645000,"text":"can cause pain."},{"time":648000,"text":"In the setting of prostate cancer,"},{"time":650000,"text":"up to 60 percent of men"},{"time":652000,"text":"after prostate cancer surgery"},{"time":654000,"text":"may have urinary incontinence"},{"time":656000,"text":"and erectile disfunction."},{"time":658000,"text":"That's a lot of people to have a lot of problems --"},{"time":661000,"text":"and this is even in"},{"time":663000,"text":"so-called nerve-sparing surgery,"},{"time":665000,"text":"which means that the surgeon is aware of the problem,"},{"time":669000,"text":"and they are trying to avoid the nerves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671000,"text":"But you know what, these little nerves are so small,"},{"time":674000,"text":"in the context of prostate cancer,"},{"time":677000,"text":"that they are actually never seen."},{"time":679000,"text":"They are traced"},{"time":681000,"text":"just by their known anatomical path"},{"time":683000,"text":"along vasculature."},{"time":685000,"text":"And they're known because somebody has decided to study them,"},{"time":689000,"text":"which means that we're still learning"},{"time":691000,"text":"about where they are."},{"time":693000,"text":"Crazy to think that we're having surgery,"},{"time":696000,"text":"we're trying to excise cancer, we don't know where the cancer is."},{"time":699000,"text":"We're trying to preserve nerves; we can't see where they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"So I said, wouldn't it be great"},{"time":704000,"text":"if we could find a way"},{"time":706000,"text":"to see nerves with fluorescence?"},{"time":709000,"text":"And at first this didn't get a lot of support."},{"time":713000,"text":"People said, \"We've been doing it this way for all these years."},{"time":715000,"text":"What's the problem?"},{"time":717000,"text":"We haven't had that many complications.\""},{"time":720000,"text":"But I went ahead anyway."},{"time":722000,"text":"And Roger helped me."},{"time":724000,"text":"And he brought his whole team with him."},{"time":727000,"text":"So there's that teamwork thing again."},{"time":731000,"text":"And we eventually discovered molecules"},{"time":734000,"text":"that were specifically labeling nerves."},{"time":736000,"text":"And when we made a solution of this,"},{"time":738000,"text":"tagged with the fluorescence"},{"time":740000,"text":"and injected in the body of a mouse,"},{"time":743000,"text":"their nerves literally glowed."},{"time":745000,"text":"You can see where they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"Here you're looking at a sciatic nerve of a mouse,"},{"time":751000,"text":"and you can see that that big, fat portion you can see very easily."},{"time":754000,"text":"But in fact, at the tip of that where I'm dissecting now,"},{"time":757000,"text":"there's actually very fine arborizations"},{"time":760000,"text":"that can't really be seen."},{"time":762000,"text":"You see what looks like little Medusa heads coming out."},{"time":766000,"text":"We have been able to see nerves"},{"time":768000,"text":"for facial expression, for facial movement, for breathing --"},{"time":771000,"text":"every single nerve --"},{"time":773000,"text":"nerves for urinary function around the prostate."},{"time":776000,"text":"We've been able to see every single nerve."},{"time":779000,"text":"When we put these two probes together ..."},{"time":783000,"text":"So here's a tumor."},{"time":785000,"text":"Do you guys know where the margins of this tumor is?"},{"time":788000,"text":"Now you do."},{"time":791000,"text":"What about the nerve that's going into this tumor?"},{"time":794000,"text":"That white portion there is easy to see."},{"time":796000,"text":"But what about the part that goes into the tumor?"},{"time":798000,"text":"Do you know where it's going?"},{"time":800000,"text":"Now you do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802000,"text":"Basically, we've come up with a way"},{"time":804000,"text":"to stain tissue"},{"time":806000,"text":"and color-code the surgical field."},{"time":808000,"text":"This was a bit of a breakthrough."},{"time":811000,"text":"I think that it'll change the way that we do surgery."},{"time":815000,"text":"We published our results"},{"time":817000,"text":"in the proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences"},{"time":819000,"text":"and in Nature Biotechnology."},{"time":821000,"text":"We received commentary in Discover magazine,"},{"time":824000,"text":"in The Economist."},{"time":826000,"text":"And we showed it to a lot of my surgical colleagues."},{"time":829000,"text":"They said, \"Wow!"},{"time":831000,"text":"I have patients"},{"time":833000,"text":"who would benefit from this."},{"time":835000,"text":"I think that this will result in my surgeries"},{"time":837000,"text":"with a better outcome"},{"time":839000,"text":"and fewer complications.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":842000,"text":"What needs to happen now"},{"time":844000,"text":"is further development of our technology"},{"time":847000,"text":"along with development"},{"time":849000,"text":"of the instrumentation"},{"time":851000,"text":"that allows us to see"},{"time":853000,"text":"this sort of fluorescence in the operating room."},{"time":856000,"text":"The eventual goal"},{"time":858000,"text":"is that we'll get this into patients."},{"time":861000,"text":"However, we've discovered"},{"time":864000,"text":"that there's actually no straightforward mechanism"},{"time":866000,"text":"to develop a molecule"},{"time":868000,"text":"for one-time use."},{"time":870000,"text":"Understandably, the majority of the medical industry"},{"time":873000,"text":"is focused on multiple-use drugs,"},{"time":877000,"text":"such as long-term daily medications."},{"time":880000,"text":"We are focused on making this technology better."},{"time":883000,"text":"We're focused on adding drugs,"},{"time":886000,"text":"adding growth factors,"},{"time":888000,"text":"killing nerves that are causing problems"},{"time":890000,"text":"and not the surrounding tissue."},{"time":893000,"text":"We know that this can be done and we're committed to doing it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":897000,"text":"I'd like to leave you with this final thought."},{"time":901000,"text":"Successful innovation"},{"time":903000,"text":"is not a single breakthrough."},{"time":906000,"text":"It is not a sprint."},{"time":909000,"text":"It is not an event for the solo runner."},{"time":913000,"text":"Successful innovation"},{"time":915000,"text":"is a team sport, it's a relay race."},{"time":918000,"text":"It requires one team for the breakthrough"},{"time":922000,"text":"and another team"},{"time":924000,"text":"to get the breakthrough accepted and adopted."},{"time":926000,"text":"And this takes the long-term steady courage"},{"time":929000,"text":"of the day-in day-out struggle"},{"time":931000,"text":"to educate, to persuade"},{"time":934000,"text":"and to win acceptance."},{"time":937000,"text":"And that is the light that I want to shine"},{"time":939000,"text":"on health and medicine today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}